subSubSection.paragraph:
Gebiacantha talismani
(
Bouvier, 1915
)

(
Figs 24
; 
25
)

Rostrum (
Fig. 24A, B
) ovoid, slightly longer than wide at base, six to eight teeth on lateral border, faint median groove on proximal half, three to five infrarostral spines; anterolateral border of carapace with four to six spines and spinules. Telson (
Fig. 24H
) approximately 1.1-1.2 times as wide as long, posterior border concave medially.

A1 peduncle (
Fig. 24C
) with lower spine on article 1; A2 peduncle (
Fig. 24D
) with two and three to five lower spines on article 3 and 4 respectively. Md (
Fig. 24E
) without mesio-anterior tooth.

P2 (
Fig. 25D
) merus with upper subdistal spine, two to four lower spinules; carpus with four or five upper spines and lower subdistal spine, propodus with upper proximal spine. P3 (
Fig. 25E
) merus with upper distal spine and four or five lower spines, carpus with lower distal spine.

Uropod exopod (
Fig. 24H
) approximately 1.2 times as long as telson.
